                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13287" author="rhasselbaum" created="Thu, 19 May 2005 02:58:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On a related note, implementing the suggested use case (i.e. decrypting properties) is very problematic with PropertyPlaceholderConfigurer because the parseString method writes the decrypted value to the log.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13289" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 19 May 2005 04:34:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report! Indeed, the convertProperties method isn&apos;t actually called anywhere... Does it show that it&apos;s been added without actually getting used? &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I&apos;ve just fixed this; the fix will be available in the next nightly build and in Spring 1.2.1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13291" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 19 May 2005 05:16:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve removed the debug logging in parseString, so that values are not logged anymore now. I&apos;ve also adapted BeanWrapperImpl to never log property values directly (which is still did for simple properties). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13292" author="rhasselbaum" created="Thu, 19 May 2005 05:36:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you. Sounds perfect.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
